cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CY 

This paper discusses a new excellence indicator in the World Report of the SCImago Institutions Rankings, which is a measure of research output and impact. The paper does not focus on a specific subfield of computer science, but rather on a general methodology for ranking institutions based on their research output. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are those that are broadly related to information retrieval, machine learning, statistics, and cybersecurity. Specifically, cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CY (Computers and Society) are all relevant sub-categories that could be associated with this paper.
